      "_id": "page.future-resources---content",
      "_type": "content",
      "html": "## Online resources ##\r\nYou will find more information about fixing housing disrepair issues on these websites. \r\n\r\n- [Advice Now](https://www.advicenow.org.uk/guides/how-fix-problems-your-privately-rented-home) offers a comprehensive guide to getting problems fixed in your rented home. \r\n\r\n- [Shelter](https://england.shelter.org.uk/housing_advice/repairs) offers specialist information for tenants with disrepair issues. \r\n\r\n- [Citizens Advice](https://www.citizensadvice.org.uk/housing/repairs-in-rented-housing/) offers practical advice and information related to housing disrepair. "
    },
    {
      "$component": true,
      "$content": true,
      "$definition": true,
      "_id": "page.future-resources---content--6",
      "_type": "content",
      "html": "## Consider organising the repair work yourself ##\r\n\r\nIf the problem is relatively small, you could arrange for the repairs to be done and take the cost out of your rent. However, it's important to keep your landlord informed, and follow a step-by-step process. You must not stop paying rent without notice. \r\n\r\nFind out more about [organising repairs yourself](https://england.shelter.org.uk/housing_advice/repairs/doing_the_repairs_if_your_landlord_wont) on the Shelter website. ",
      "show": {
