      "_id": "page.future-resources---content--7",
      "_type": "content",
      "html": "## Making complaints about landlords, letting agents and the local council \r\n\r\nIf you're unhappy with the way your landlord, letting agent or local council have dealt with the problem, you can make a complaint. \r\n\r\nFind out more about [making complaints](/complaints)"
    },
    {
      "_id": "page.future-resources---content--8",
      "_type": "content",
      "html": "**Go [back to the 'What to do now'](/what-to-do-now) page.** "
    },
    {
      "_id": "page.future-resources---content--9",
      "_type": "content",
      "html": "## Mental health resources \r\n\r\nYou said the problem had affected your mental health. You may want to consider speaking to your GP or one of the charities listed below for support.\r\n\r\n\r\n- [Hub of hope](https://hubofhope.co.uk/) directs you to mental health support and resources in your area.\r\n\r\n- [Mind](https://www.mind.org.uk/) provides help and support for people experiencing mental health problems.  \r\n\r\n- [NHS mental health support](https://www.nhs.uk/mental-health/get-urgent-help-for-mental-health/) gives mental health support information, including where to get urgent help. \r\n\r\n- [Samaritans](https://www.samaritans.org/) 24hr phone line for people to talk through problems of all kinds. Call 116 123.\r\n\r\n- [Sane line](http://www.sane.org.uk/what_we_do/support/helpline) SANEline is a national out-of-hours mental health helpline. \r\n",
